     <subsection xml:id="subsec-Solving-angles-of-polygons">
        <title>Solving angles of polygons</title>
            <activity>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        What you need: Cuts-outs of polygons, a ruler and a protractor.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                    1. (a) Measure the interior angles of each polygon.   
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        (b) Work out the sum of the interior angles of each polygon.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        2.(a) What is the sum of the exterior angles of each polygon?
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        (b) Work out the value of one exterior angle of each polygon using the formula, 
                                        <me>\frac{360^\circ}{n}.</me>
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        3. Add each exterior angle to its corresponding interior angle. What do you notice?
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Connect.
                    </p>


                            <p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            If a polygon has n sides, the number of triangles is <m>n-2</m>.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            The sum of the interior angles in a polygon = number of triangles <m>\times 180^\circ</m>                                                                
                                        </p>

                                        <p>
                                            <me>180^\circ\times (n-2) </me>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            To get the size of one interior angle in a regular polygon, divide the sum of the interior angles by the number of sides.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <me>\frac{90^\circ\times (2n-4)}{n}=\frac{180^\circ\times (n-2)}{n} </me>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Size of exterior angle <m>=\frac{360^\circ}{n}</m>.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Exterior angle + its corresponding interior angle <m>=180^\circ.</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </p>
                </statement>
            </activity>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A regular polygon has six sides.determine:
                </p>
                <tabular>
                    <row>
                        <cell>(a) The size of each interior angle </cell>
                        <cell> (b) The size of each exterior angle.</cell>
                    </row>
                </tabular>
                
            </statement>
         <solution>
            <p>
                (a) sum of interior angles is <me>
                    (2n-4)\times 90^\circ=(2 \times 6-4)\times 90^\circ  </me>   
            </p>

            <p>
                <me>=(12-4)\times 90^\circ    </me>
           </p>

           <p>
                <me>
                   = 8 \times 90^\circ
                </me>
           </p>

           <p>
                <me>
                 =720^\circ   
                </me>  
           </p>

           <p>
            size of each interior angle <me>
               = \frac{720^\circ}{6}  </me> 
           </p>

           <p>
                <me>
                   = 120^\circ
                </me>
          </p>

          <p>
            (b).Size of each exterior angle is <me>
               = \frac{360^\circ}{n}=\frac{360}{6}
            </me> 
          </p>

          <p>
                <me>
                   = 60^\circ
                </me>
            
          </p>

         </solution>
        </example>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    The sum of the interior angles of a regular polygon is <m>540^\circ.</m> Deterimine the number of sides of the polygon.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <m>(2n-4) \times 90^\circ = 540^\circ</m>
                </p>

                <p>
                    <m>180n-360^\circ=540^\circ</m>
                </p>

                <p>
                    <m>180n-360^\circ+360^\circ=540^\circ+360^\circ</m>
                </p>

                <p>
                    <me>180n=900^\circ</me>
                </p>

                <p>
                    <me>n=5</me>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>

    </subsection>
